				<header>
	<h2 class="bloc-title">4. Data transfer</h2>
</header>
<br/>
				<p>
					Your username and avatar as registered within the Platform will automatically be displayed to the public when You chose to upload videos onto the Platform.<br/><br/>VIOUSLY may, from time to time, contact You on behalf of external business partners about a particular offering that may be of interest to You. In those cases, the Data (e-mail, name, address, telephone number) will only be transferred to the third party, including without limitation certain information received from Your social media platform login, upon Your prior authorization.<br/><br/>VIOUSLY may also share the Data with trusted partners to help perform statistical analysis, send You email or postal mail, provide customer support, or arrange for deliveries. All such third parties are prohibited from using Your personal information except to provide these services to VIOUSLY, and they are required to maintain the strict confidentiality of the Data.<br/><br/>Other than set forth herein, VIOUSLY does not sell, rent or lease the Data to third parties.<br/><br/>Other than set forth herein, VIOUSLY does not sell, rent or lease the Data to third parties.
				</p>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article class="card scrollspy" id="privacy-cookie">
			<div class="card-content">
				<header>
	<h2 class="bloc-title">5. Use of Cookies/Targeted Advertising</h2>
</header>
<br/>
				<p>
					VIOUSLY or third parties authorized by VIOUSLY (such as advertisers and analytics companies), may use tracking technology such as "cookies" to help personalize Your online experience. A cookie is a text file that is placed on Your hard disk by a web page server. Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to Your computer. Cookies are uniquely assigned to You, and can only be read by a web server in the domain that issued the cookie to You.<br/><br/>You have the ability to accept or decline cookies by indicating Your choice in the cookie banner displayed when connecting to the Site and/or the Platform. If You choose to decline cookies, You may not be able to fully experience the interactive features of the Services and/or the Site.<br/><br/>You can choose to limit Behavioral Advertising on the Site by accessing the following URL address: <a href="http://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank">http://www.aboutads.info/choices/</a> and opting-out of cookies placed by those vendors listed. After You opt-out, You will still see advertisements but the advertising may not be as relevant to Your interests. If You change Your computer, change Your browser, or delete Your cookies, You will need to renew Your opt-out.
				</p>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article class="card scrollspy" id="privacy-data-security">
			<div class="card-content">
				<header>
	<h2 class="bloc-title">6. Security and storage of the Data</h2>
</header>
<br/>
				<p>
					VIOUSLY secures the Data from unauthorized access, use and/or disclosure by unauthorized third parties and ensures that will take all appropriate measures to limit the risk that it may be lost, damaged or misused.<br/><br/>Data is stored on secured third party servers in France. The Data is kept only as long as necessary for the purposes set out above. Upon termination of such purposes, Data is kept only for statistical and evidence purposes and shall not be used for any other reason. Once such period is expired, the Data is destroyed.
				</p>
				</div>
			</article>
